##The taste of vegetables

WECHAT denganqing1984

Feature description, here, I will share my writing, reading the book.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Speaking of staying in my hometown for so long, I always have friends outside asking me: "How are you doing there? Are you okay? " I replied to them: "I dare not say anything else, the food is enough. " Indeed, never have I eaten so many vegetables like this year: Cabbage, Shanghai Greens, Cai Tai... every meal is always the same vegetarian, plus some fish. My mother was always worried that I didn't eat well because I hardly ate any of the meat dishes. I told her not to worry, "I eat outside every day so big fish big meat, early eat tired of it. Or the house these dishes delicious. "

Mother thought I was trying to coax her, but she was relieved to see that I could have two bowls of green vegetable soup. It's not that you don't eat vegetables in Beijing, but they're not fresh or tasty. My mother laughed again and said, "when you were a child, you didn't like vegetables at all, but now you want them at every meal! " I finished my last mouthful of Soup and put down the bowl and chopsticks, "only by comparison can I feel it. After eating out for so many years, eating in the house is just delicious. "

The outbreak is so severe that no one can leave the house. Only the kitchen garden behind the house, when nothing to go around, is also a lookout. Especially early in the morning, the fog dispersed, Shanghai Green Oval leaves in the breeze, insects crawling under the roots of vegetables, turnips pull up when the dirt fell on the ground... the mood will be a lot better.

Think of the brother family in the city, want to eat some vegetables, but also with the purchase of supplies pass to the supermarket queue for two hours to be able to buy. And we in the countryside hometown, wants to eat to go to the vegetable garden to pick, most fresh, also most water ling, eats also most relaxed. In fact, my mother had prepared a lot of food to bring to my brother and his family, but because people are now restricted, had to give up.

Vegetables picked from the garden every day

Although the vegetables are delicious, I worry when I eat them, "WHAT IF WE RUN OUT OF VEGETABLES IN THE GARDEN? After all, our garden is so big."The mother said:"That won't, we must hurry to eat, don't eat, you see this all want heart elder. Even after I had eaten it, I was not afraid. I still had two sides planted in the lake field."I asked my mother why she had planted so many, the mother smiled a way: "anyway farming is not worth money, as many kinds of dishes. Now vegetables a few miles, I eat their own, a few off, a few convenient. "

The family had rented a room on the ground floor of a neighborhood where their parents lived, to care for their two nephews who were studying downtown. My father goes to the park for nothing, while my mother, who is concerned about the family's acres of land, often comes back to work while her nephews are at school.

Since then, my mother has been growing more vegetables in the field, so she doesn't have to pay for them at the market. With a good crop and a good harvest, my mother took bags of vegetables to the city, not only to eat at home, but also to share turnips, green peppers, vegetables, Pumpkins and other neighbors who also came to rent.

The neighbors, in turn, were good to her. If my mother is not feeling well, a neighbor will bring medicine. If the electric appliance is broken, someone in front will come and help to fix it. Sometimes we will make dumplings together. My mother won't. The grandmother on the right will teach my mother how to roll the skin, how to wrap up a good look... these renters, mostly for the children to read from the countryside, so with the mother to talk.

This part of my mother's life, I did not experience. My mother was not there to see my life in Beijing. Think of Beijing a few days ago still under heavy snow, everywhere bleak, green can not be seen. I might as well stay home now and wait for spring.

Green, eyeful of green, is my favorite place of the old home bar. But every New Year's Day comes and goes in a hurry. And almost as long as the New Year that few days, are miserable. Now drowned stay at home for so long, gradually see spring really come, and not long after the rape flowers should open.

Go to the fields with my mother, green everywhere
